org.opendaylight.controller.networkconfig.neutron

Interface INeutronSubnetAware


  • public interface INeutronSubnetAware
    This interface defines the methods a service that wishes to be aware of Neutron Subnets needs to implement

    • Method Detail

      • canCreateSubnet

        int canCreateSubnet(NeutronSubnet subnet)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified subnet can be created
        Parameters:
        subnet - instance of proposed new Neutron Subnet object
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the create operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • neutronSubnetCreated

        void neutronSubnetCreated(NeutronSubnet subnet)
        Services provide this interface method for taking action after a subnet has been created
        Parameters:
        subnet - instance of new Neutron Subnet object

      • canUpdateSubnet

        int canUpdateSubnet(NeutronSubnet delta,
                  NeutronSubnet original)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified subnet can be changed using the specified delta
        Parameters:
        delta - updates to the subnet object using patch semantics
        subnet - instance of the Neutron Subnet object to be updated
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the update operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • neutronSubnetUpdated

        void neutronSubnetUpdated(NeutronSubnet subnet)
        Services provide this interface method for taking action after a subnet has been updated
        Parameters:
        subnet - instance of modified Neutron Subnet object

      • canDeleteSubnet

        int canDeleteSubnet(NeutronSubnet subnet)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified subnet can be deleted
        Parameters:
        subnet - instance of the Subnet Router object to be deleted
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the delete operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.
